The equilibrium of the universe is referred to in the following short Ayat:

“The sun and the moon follow courses (exactly) computed; And the star and the trees - both (alike) bow in adoration. And the Firmament has He raised high, and He has set up the Balance (of Justice).” (Surah 55, Ayah 5-7)

In the great mathematical universe, there are great mathematical laws that require calculations. We now understand that these Ayat refer to the laws discovered by Kepler and Newton. ♦ Balance of Justice between humans.

♦ The heavens themselves are sustained by Divine equilibrium.

Julian and Lunar Calendars

The Muslim calendar is based upon the moon, which revolves around the earth in periods of about 29 days. That first day was 16 June 622 of the Julian calendar.

It was correct to address them in the only language they could understand and not to upset their habits.
